  "text": "Blood and plasma metabolites. Blood glucose concentration was measured on an ABL 615 (Radiometer Medical, Brønshøj, Denmark). Plasma glycerol (Beckman Coulter, County Clare, Ireland) and plasma triacylglycerol (TG; GPO-PAP kit) concentrations were measured using enzymatic colorimetric methods (Hitachi 912 automatic analyzer; Boehringer Mannheim, Indianapolis, IN). Plasma TG concentration was calculated as plasma TG minus free plasma glycerol. Whole cell lysate preparation. Freeze-dried and dissected muscle tissue was homogenized as described previously [CITATION_1] . Homogenates were rotated end over end for 1 h at 4°C and then cleared by centrifugation for 20 min (16,000 g, 4°C).",
